A: Did you finish reading the magazine?

13
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,000
B: I'm still working it。

14
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,600
C: Did you fix my car?   D: I'm still working on it.  

15
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:42,720
A: you could say “I'm still working on it” means… M: I still need more time. A: Fantastic. M: Great. Okay, it's clear.

16
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:58,320
A: I have another one for you guys, it's a phrase commonly used and you'll hear it all the  time – coke and fries.  M: Coke and fries.  A: Coke and fries. M: Coke and fries. It's a short way of saying “Coca-Cola and French fries".   

17
